<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-09T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="792" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d792">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/3008a: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss> to the Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi></persName>)</head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-09T18:00:00-05:00">December 9, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                                    </dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>145. An Associated Press despatch from Addis Ababa states that
                                    representatives of the International Red Cross there have sent a
                                    formal protest to the League concerning the bombing of the
                                    American Seventh Day Adventist hospital at Dessye. A Reuters
                                    despatch from the same place states merely that seven doctors
                                    there have executed an affidavit concerning the bombing. A
                                    United Press despatch states that seven doctors have issued a
                                    formal protest.</p>
                                <p>Please telegraph any pertinent information available in Geneva,
                                    also whether International Red Cross authorities there recognize
                                    that hospital as being affiliated with their organization.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>